{"questionId":"3464356","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>correct probability equation&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>length</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>length</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept any letter instead of “length” e.g., <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>normal curve with vertical lines symmetrical about the mean line with a correct indication of an area of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/777712ea374e19a371ccf8680801af798b66ea08.png\"></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>210</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>210405</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)A0</strong> </em>for an answer of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/